# Wildcards & PECS

## Generics are invariant

- `List<Integer>` is **not** a `List<Number>` — and that's correct

## Opt in at the use site

- `? extends T` — **covariant**, read-only (producer)
- `? super T` — **contravariant**, write-friendly (consumer)

```java
sumAll(List<? extends Number> list)      // read T
fillWithIntegers(List<? super Integer>)  // add T
```

## PECS

- **Producer Extends, Consumer Super** — `copy(List<? super T> dest, List<? extends T> src)`
